</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:58
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='407000' id='t-407000'>Go back to this image of the axe and the mouse,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='410000' id='t-410000'>and ask yourself: &quot;Who made them and for who?&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='413000' id='t-413000'>The stone axe was made by someone for himself.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='415000' id='t-415000'>It was self-sufficiency.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='417000' id='t-417000'>We call that poverty these days.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='419000' id='t-419000'>But the object on the right</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='421000' id='t-421000'>was made for me by other people.</span>
