<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='484000' id='t-484000'>than Louis XIV even had.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='486000' id='t-486000'>And that's what we've done, because we're all working for each other.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='489000' id='t-489000'>We're able to draw upon specialization and exchange</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='492000' id='t-492000'>to raise each other's living standards.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:26
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='495000' id='t-495000'>Now, you do get other animals working for each other too.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='498000' id='t-498000'>Ants are a classic example; workers work for queens and queens work for workers.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='501000' id='t-501000'>But there's a big difference,</span>
